<p>This is what I want:</p>  <pre><code>public class CustomRealmMigration implements RealmMigration {     // Current version     private static final long SCHEMA_VERSION = 4;      private final Context mContext;      public CustomRealmMigration(Context context) {         mContext = context;     }      @Override     public long execute(Realm realm, long version) {         if (SCHEMA_VERSION &lt; version) {             // Rollback, not allow             deleteRealm();             return SCHEMA_VERSION;         }         return version;     }      private void deleteRealm() {         RealmConfiguration realmConfiguration = new RealmConfiguration.Builder(mContext)                 .name(Realm.DEFAULT_REALM_NAME)                 .build();         Realm.deleteRealm(realmConfiguration);     } } </code></pre>  <p>with error:</p>  <pre><code>Caused by: java.lang.IllegalStateException: It's not allowed to delete the file associated with an open Realm. Remember to close() all the instances of the Realm before deleting its file. </code></pre>  <p>How to delete Realm while migrating? Or how to get old version of Realm elsewhere?</p>